#  GitHub Pull Request (PR) Template

---

## 1. Purpose
This document establishes a standardized pull request (PR) template to ensure consistent documentation of changes, support Agile traceability, and factilitate efficient review and approval processes. 

## 2. Scope
This SOP applies to all project team members submitting pull requests withing the GitHub repository. 

This document covers:
- Pull Request creation
- Commity message formatting
- PR title conventions
- Documentation and review requirements

This SOP will apply to both code and documentation changes. 

## 4. Definitions
- **Pull Request (PR):** A request to merge changes from one branch into another
- **Agile Traceability:** Linking work to user stories, tasks, or backlog items
- **Commit Message:** A description of changes associated with a code or documentation update

## 5. Roles and Responsibilities

| Role | Responsibility |
|------|---------------|
| Contributor | Creates PRs in accordance with this SOP |
| Reviewer | Reviews PRs for accuracy, completeness, and compliance |
| Software Development Lead | Approves PRs and ensures alignment with requirements |
| Technical Writer | Maintains documentation standards and templates |

## 6. Pull Request Standards

All pull requests will contain the following:

- Follow the required title and commit message format
- Include Agile traceability (e.g., ticket or user story)
- Provide a clear description of changes
- Address documentation impact

## 7. Pull Request Title and Commit Message Requirements

### 7.1 Standard Format 

**Format:**

[TYPE][TICKET-ID]: Short description

**Examples:**

- [DOC][ACRIME-101]: Update template document
- [FIX][ACRIME-102]: Correct database response. 

---

### 7.2 Accepted Type Values

- **DOC** - Documentation changes
- **FEAT** - New feature
- **FIX** - Bug fix
- **REFACTOR** - Code restructuring
- **CHORE** - Maintenance tasks

---

### 7.3 Requirements
- PR titles will follow the standard format
- Each commit message shall follow the standard format
- Descriptions shall be concise and meaningful

---

## 8. Pull Request Process

### 8.1 Create Branch

- Create a feature branch from the main developement branch

---

### 8.2 Make Changes

- Implement code or documentation updates
- Ensure alighment with requirements and standards

---

### 8.3 Commit Changes

- Use the required commit message format
- Group related changes logically

---

### 8.4 Submit Pull Request

- Open a Pull Request (PR) in Github
- Ensure the PR template is fully completed

---

### 8.5 Review Process

Reviewers shall evaluate:

- Accuracy
- Completeness
- Clarity
- Compliance with standards

---

### 8.6 Address Feedback

- Update PR based on reviewer comments
- Maintain clear communication in PR discussion

---

### 8.7 Approval and Merge
- Obtain required approvals
- Merge PR according to project workflow

---

